data.chText: 她很能体谅他人的感情。
data.enText: She is very sensitive to other people's feelings.

data.enText: easily offended or upset

information/subject
that you have to treat with great care because it may offend people or make them angry

data.chText: 医疗卫生是政界的一个敏感问题。
data.enText: Health care is a politically sensitive issue.
to cold/light/food, etc.
reacting quickly or more than usual to sth
sensitive areas of the body
My teeth are very sensitive to cold food.
to small changes
able to measure very small changes
a sensitive instrument

data.chText: 证券市场对政局变化非常敏感。
data.enText: The Stock Exchange is very sensitive to political change.

data.chText: 她谨慎细致地处理了那件事情。
data.enText: She handled the matter sensitively.
He writes sensitively.
hit/touch a (raw/sensitive) nerve
to mention a subject that makes sb feel angry, upset, embarrassed, etc.

data.chText: 你谈起他的第一个妻子，这就触到了他的痛处。
data.enText: You touched a raw nerve when you mentioned his first wife.

data.chText: sensible和sensitive与sense的两个不同含义相联系。
data.enText: Sensible and sensitive are connected with two different meanings of sense.
Sensible refers to your ability to make good judgements.

data.chText: 她给了我一些非常合理的建议。
data.enText: She gave me some very sensible advice.

data.chText: 这么晚一个人单独外出是不太明智的。
data.enText: It wasn’t very sensible to go out on your own so late at night.
Sensitive refers to how easily you react to things and how much you are aware of things or other people.
a soap for sensitive skin

data.chText: 这部影片可能使易冲动的孩子感到难过。
data.enText: This movie may upset a sensitive child.

tr: someone who serves as an intermediary between the living and the dead
of or pertaining to classified information or matters affecting national security

example: the tender spot on his jaw
the more sensible parts of the skin
a mimosa's leaves are sensitive to touch

tr: being susceptible to the attitudes, feelings, or circumstances of others
example: sensitive to the local community and its needs

value.def: If you are sensitive to other people's needs, problems, or feelings, you show understanding and awareness of them.

example.ex: The classroom teacher must be sensitive to a child's needs...
example.tran: 班主任必须对小学生的需求体察入微。

example.ex: He was always so sensitive and caring.
example.tran: 他总是如此理解和关心别人。

value.tran: 体恤的;体贴的;善解人意的

example.ex: The abuse of women needs to be treated seriously and sensitively.
example.tran: 虐待妇女问题需要得到严肃而认真的处理。

example.ex: A good relationship involves concern and sensitivity for each other's feelings.
example.tran: 一段美满的恋情需要彼此关心并体恤对方的情感。

value.def: If you are sensitive about something, you are easily worried and offended when people talk about it.

example.ex: Young people are very sensitive about their appearance...
Take it easy. Don't be so sensitive.

value.tran: 易生气的;易担忧的;敏感的

example.ex: ...people who suffer extreme sensitivity about what others think...
example.tran: 对别人的想法过分在意的人们

example.ex: They are aware of American political sensitivities about their country's role.
example.tran: 他们明白美国人对其国家扮演的政治角色很敏感。

value.def: A sensitive subject or issue needs to be dealt with carefully because it is likely to cause disagreement or make people angry or upset.

example.ex: Employment is a very sensitive issue.
example.tran: 就业是一个非常棘手的问题。

value.tran: (问题、话题)敏感的，棘手的，易引起纷争的，须谨慎对待的

example.ex: Due to the obvious sensitivity of the issue he would not divulge any details.
example.tran: 由于该问题明显非常敏感，他不会透露任何细节。

value.def: Sensitive documents or reports contain information that needs to be kept secret and dealt with carefully.

example.ex: He instructed staff to shred sensitive documents.
example.tran: 他吩咐员工将机密文件用碎纸机销毁。

example.ex: ...sensitive information which, in the wrong hands, could jeopardise the safety of British troops.
example.tran: 落入敌人手中会危及英军安全的机要情报

value.tran: (文件、报告)机密的，须小心对待的，须妥善保管的

value.def: Something that is sensitive to a physical force, substance, or treatment is easily affected by it and often harmed by it.

example.ex: ...a chemical which is sensitive to light.

example.tran: 适用于敏感性皮肤的温和化妆品

value.tran: 过敏的;易受影响的;敏感的

example.ex: ...the sensitivity of cells to damage by chemotherapy.
example.tran: 细胞很容易受化疗损伤

value.def: A sensitive piece of scientific equipment is capable of measuring or recording very small changes.
value.tran: (科学仪器)灵敏的，灵敏度高的

partsOfSpeech.dec: as 加强 + sent 感觉 → 感觉一样 → 赞成
con 共同 + sens 感觉 + us 表名词，用于科学术语 → 感觉相同 → 一致意见
con 共同 + sent 感觉 → 同感 → 同意
consent 同意 + ient …的 → 同意的；一致的
dis 分离 + sent 感觉 → 感觉有分歧 → 持不同意见
dis 分离 + sens 感觉 + ion 表状态 → 意见不合
non 无 + sense 感觉 → 没有感觉 → 无意义的话
pre 预先 + senti〔= sent〕感觉 + ment 表名词 → 预感
re 相反 + sent 感觉 → 反感 → 怨恨
resent 怨恨 + ment 表名词 → 怨恨
sens 感觉 + ibility 易…性 → 敏感性；感情
sens 感觉 + ible 能…的 → 能感觉的；明智的
sens 感觉 + itive …的 → 敏感的
sens 感觉 + ory …的 → 感觉的
senti〔= sent〕感觉 + ment 表名词 → 感觉 → 感情
sentiment 感情 + al …的 → 多感情的；感伤的

argument 争论 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 好争吵的
authority 权威 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 权威性的
cogn 知道 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 认知的
compete 比赛；竞争 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 比赛的；竞争的
define 下定义 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 确定的
inform 通知 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 提供情报的
meditate 沉思 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 沉思的
preserve 保存 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 防腐的
prime 最初，原始 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 原始的
pun 惩罚 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 刑罚的
repeat 重复 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 重复的
represent 作…的代表 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 有代表性的
sense 感觉 + itive 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 敏感的
talk 讲话 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 爱说话的，健谈的
